Role Summary
· Performs a variety of operational work in the development, installation, and maintenance of the OFC transmission and distribution network.

Duties and Responsibilities
· Successfully handle all assigned fiber optic O&M work and meet the needs of customers;
· Troubleshoot and negotiate customer issues and complaints;
· Fiber optic cable laying both in backbone and access network;
· Schedule fiber cable laying and repairing project and ensure the completion within estimating cost and time;
· Optical fiber cable deploying, blowing, splicing and testing;
· Experienced by using below tools are required;
§ Splicing machine
§ OTDR
§ Splicing Machine
§ Laser Source
§ Power Meter
§ Light Source (VFL)
§ Cable Locator
§ OFC Media Tester
· Delegate the tasks efficiently within the team so as to meet SLAs well within the time limits;
· Performing OFC site survey;
· Coordination with ROW Authorities to obtain Permission and prevent fiber cuts;
· Having good relationship with the customers;
· Have a positive attitude in carrying out his duties for AFTEL;
· Attend meeting when required;
· Effectively prioritize and execute tasks in a high-pressure environment;
· Executing any other tasks assign by line manager;

Job Requirements
· University degree in Telecom / Information Technology/ Computer Science with minimum of 3 years of experience in the field of OFC transmission network.
Required skills and knowledge:
· Having SDH, MSTP, DWDM and OTN concept and knowledge.
· OFC Transmission equipment configuration and troubleshooting skills
· CCNA level network Knowledge;
· Hand on experience in OFC transmission network troubleshooting.

Submission Guidelines
متقاضیان میتوانند cv یا خلص صوانح شانرا به ایمیل آدرس های hr@afghantelecom.af با ذکر نمبر بست (OFC-Cont-17) و عنوان بست درموضوع ایمیل ارسال نمایند. متقاضیانیکه درخواستی خویش را بعد از تاریخ اعلان بست ارسال مینمایند و یا هم شرایط مندرج این بست را تکمیل ننمایند شامل پروسه امتحان تحریری و مصاحبه نمیگردند.
